Prague transport company delivers chip card for the first time on Wednesday
October 1, 2008 Wednesday marks the date in the history of the Prague Transport Company when the first passenger will board metros, trams and buses, who will have an electronic coupon in his pocket instead of a paper ticket.
The coupon is currently available to approximately 100,000 people who own an Opencard chip card.
Passengers can purchase a 30-day, 90-day and annual voucher (valid from 1 January 2009) and save it to their smartcard at the information centres and branches of the Transport Company at the Muzeum, M<0xC5><0xAF>stek, Nádra<0xC5><0xBE><0xC3><0xAD> Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice, And<0xC4><0x9B>l, Roztyly, Let<0xC5><0x88>any, Kobylisy, Kabyle<0xC4><0x8D>e, Rajská zahrada
The coupons can be purchased via the website of the Transport Company www.dpp.cz as of yesterday.
The service was used by more than 400 customers until the afternoon hours.
Those who start using the internet can finally forget about the publishing windows of metro stations, where they have had to stand regularly long lines for line tickets.
The coupon can be purchased over the Internet and saved on the Opencard card in one of the thirteen branches of the City Library.
“At these locations, passengers have access to a desk with trained servers to assist those interested in online shopping and to save their purchased coupons on their cards,” said Martin Opatrn<0xC3><0xBD>, project spokesman.
In addition to libraries, electronic coupons can be saved to Opencard in the self-service vending machines installed in some foyers.
What do these machines look like?
They are red, reminiscent of ticket offices and passengers may have already noticed them at Roztyly, Bud<0xC4><0x9B>jovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro stations.
"There are currently five of them in the city, but it should be 80 by the end of the year," Opatrn<0xC3><0xBD> added.
The coupon is checked by an automatic instead of the driver
The machines that start working tomorrow are easy to operate.
Simply insert the Opencard chip card and the previously paid coupon will be saved on its own.
From tomorrow, electronic coupons will be valid not only in the capital, but also in its surroundings.
So, on the trains and bus lines around the city from 300 to 499, by which mainly residents of the central Czech districts travel to the capital.
