Heinz-Christian Strache, of the right-wing Austrian Freedom Party, and Filip Dewinter, of the Belgian right-wing party, Vlaams Belang, took part in a demonstration in Antwerp on Thursday, 17 January 2008, at which the organization "Cities Against the Islamic Conquest" was introduced.
They paraded with signs imitating traffic signs depicting mosques crossed by red lines.
According to police, far-right extremists are responsible for the defamation of Muslim cemeteries in Austria, which happened on the same weekend that far-right parties made significant headway in national parliamentary elections.
More than 90 graves were severely damaged in the Traun cemetery near Linz sometime between Friday night and this morning, according to police.
The perpetrators spray-painted Jewish symbols, such as the Star of David, on some graves, but investigators said they were only trying to hide their extreme motives, which stem from their hatred of Muslim immigrants.
